    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was very disappointed to read your review and I am sorry if you felt that the nurses didn't care. I can assure you that they do care and that they would not have wanted you or your wife to be upset. I understand that after you were asked to leave the ward the Head of Clinical Services did speak to you and she arranged for you to go back and see your wife for a little while. I was also pleased to hear that your wife made a good recovery from her surgery and that she was discharged home later the same day. 
Your wife was admitted for surgery into a shared room and in respect for patient privacy we do have set visiting hours. We do, however, do our best to accommodate our patients wishes and if we had known, in advance, that you wanted to stay with your wife we would have done our best to accommodate her in a single room. We aim to give quality care to our patients and provide them with the best possible experience. Please accept my apologies that you were not happy with your experience. Regards Kathie Rimmer Hospital Director  
